article.headline: SE Louisiana 79, Spring Hill 65
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Quennell Green scored 19 points to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 79-65 win over Spring Hill Thursday night, giving coach Jim Yarbrough his 100th career win. Ricky Woods added 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Lions (3-1). Chris Lee had 14 points and Scott Roniger dished out 13 assists. Krisner Green led Spring Hill (2-2) with 34 points and was 17-of-18 from the free-throw line. Chris Baldwin added 23 points and both he and Green pulled down eight rebounds. Southeastern Louisiana led 41-29 at the half. Yarbrough has a 100-43 record overall and is in his sixth season at Southeastern Louisiana.
